docs.abstract: Consoler in chief has been a role that President Trump has been slow and somewhat reluctant to embrace — especially in contrast to his predecessor.
docs.snippet: Consoler in chief has been a role that President Trump has been slow and somewhat reluctant to embrace — especially in contrast to his predecessor.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — For more than an hour on Wednesday, President Trump listened quietly to entreaties for action, personal stories of grief and loss, and expressions of raw anger, clutching a white notecard with talking points written on it.

headline.main: What Do Jotted Talking Points Say About Trump’s Empathy?
headline.print_headline: On Notecard, a Reminder for the President to Show Compassion to Survivors

docs.abstract: The Treasury Department announced new sanctions on North Korea as the administration continues to crack down on the nuclear ambitions of Kim Jong-un.
docs.snippet: The Treasury Department announced new sanctions on North Korea as the administration continues to crack down on the nuclear ambitions of Kim Jong-un.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration unfurled new sanctions on Wednesday targeting North Korea and its weapons program, underscoring the aggressive approach that President Trump has promised to take against the government of Kim Jong-un.

headline.main: Trump Administration Slaps New Sanctions on North Korea
headline.print_headline: U.S. Orders New Batch Of Sanctions on Kim

docs.abstract: The president, goaded by conservatives, is targeting an effort to address racial disparities in school discipline, arguing that any relaxation of policies could let a killer slip through the cracks.
docs.snippet: The president, goaded by conservatives, is targeting an effort to address racial disparities in school discipline, arguing that any relaxation of policies could let a killer slip through the cracks.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — After a gunman marauded through Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School last month, conservative commentators — looking for a culprit — seized on an unlikely target: an Obama-era guidance document that sought to rein in the suspensions and expulsions of minority students.

headline.main: Trump Finds Unlikely Culprit in School Shootings: Obama Discipline Policies
headline.print_headline: Trump Points to Culprit in School Shootings, and It Isn’t Guns

docs.abstract: Representative K. Michael Conaway of Texas had said the Russians hadn’t favored Donald J. Trump’s candidacy. But on Tuesday, he said it was a matter of interpretation.
docs.snippet: Representative K. Michael Conaway of Texas had said the Russians hadn’t favored Donald J. Trump’s candidacy. But on Tuesday, he said it was a matter of interpretation.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Republican leading the House Intelligence Committee’s investigation into Russian election interference softened his characterization of a key investigative finding on Tuesday, just a day after Republicans announced that they had completed a draft of their report.

headline.main: Republican Leading House’s Russia Inquiry Softens a Key Finding
headline.print_headline: House Leader Retreats On Russian Election Role

keywords.value: Russian Interference in 2016 US Elections and Ties to Trump Associates

docs.abstract: After a made-for-television moment in which he appeared to embrace expansive gun control, President Trump completed his reversal on Monday.
docs.snippet: After a made-for-television moment in which he appeared to embrace expansive gun control, President Trump completed his reversal on Monday.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump on Monday abandoned his promise to work for gun control measures opposed by the National Rifle Association, bowing to the gun group and embracing its agenda of armed teachers and incremental improvements to the background check system.

headline.main: Conceding to N.R.A., Trump Abandons Brief Gun Control Promise
headline.print_headline: Trump Retreats From Promises On Gun Control

byline.original: By Michael D. Shear and Sheryl Gay Stolberg

docs.abstract: “I’m not a racist. I’m the least racist person you will ever interview, that I can tell you,” President Trump said in Florida.
docs.snippet: “I’m not a racist. I’m the least racist person you will ever interview, that I can tell you,” President Trump said in Florida.
docs.lead_paragraph: PALM BEACH, Fla. — President Trump declared on Sunday night that he was “not a racist” and insisted that the derogatory comment attributed to him during an Oval Office meeting on immigration last week did not occur.

headline.main: ‘I’m Not a Racist,’ Trump Says in Denying Vulgar Comment

docs.abstract: The Trump administration is being forced to rethink strategies that were driven largely by military considerations.
docs.snippet: The Trump administration is being forced to rethink strategies that were driven largely by military considerations.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump, by demanding on Friday that European allies agree to rewrite the Iran nuclear deal within 120 days or he will kill it, set himself a diplomatic challenge that would be formidable even for an administration with a deep bench of experienced negotiators.

headline.main: Trump’s Demand to Rewrite Iran Deal Tests a Weakened Diplomatic Corps
headline.print_headline: Demand on Iran Deal Tests Diplomatic Corps

docs.abstract: The outcome of a procedural vote signals that the bill has sufficient support to pass in the Senate.
docs.snippet: The outcome of a procedural vote signals that the bill has sufficient support to pass in the Senate.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate cleared the path on Tuesday for Congress to extend the National Security Agency’s warrantless surveillance program for six years with minimal changes, rejecting bipartisan calls to first vote on amendments that would have imposed significant new privacy protections when the program sweeps up Americans’ emails.

headline.main: Senate, Rebuffing Privacy Concerns, Clears Path to Extend Surveillance Law
headline.print_headline: Warrantless Surveillance Is Headed for Renewal

docs.abstract: Politicians and other well-wishers gathered at the Capitol Wednesday to pay tribute to the Rev. Billy Graham, ahead of his funeral in North Carolina on Friday.
docs.snippet: Politicians and other well-wishers gathered at the Capitol Wednesday to pay tribute to the Rev. Billy Graham, ahead of his funeral in North Carolina on Friday.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The line of mourners snaked through the Capitol: little children resting on their parents’ shoulders, retirees from North Carolina, the manager of a recreational vehicle dealership who flew in from Houston, the leader of a Muslim Boy Scout troop in Virginia. They filed past the plain pine plywood coffin in the grand Capitol Rotunda, some weeping, most in quiet contemplation.

headline.main: Rev. Billy Graham Lies in Honor at U.S. Capitol for Day of Remembrance
headline.print_headline: At Capitol, A Nation Pays Tribute To Graham

byline.original: By Sheryl Gay Stolberg and Michael D. Shear

docs.abstract: In an interview, Senator Mitch McConnell said that Mitt Romney’s Senate run was an illustration of Republicans’ improving fortunes entering a challenging midterm campaign.
docs.snippet: In an interview, Senator Mitch McConnell said that Mitt Romney’s Senate run was an illustration of Republicans’ improving fortunes entering a challenging midterm campaign.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Mitch McConnell said in an interview on Friday afternoon that President Trump should rally behind the Senate candidacy of Mitt Romney despite his blistering criticism in 2016, arguing that Mr. Romney’s potent bid was an illustration of the Republican Party’s improving fortunes entering a challenging midterm campaign.

headline.main: Trump Should Get Behind Romney’s Candidacy, McConnell Says
headline.print_headline: Trump Should Support Romney’s Candidacy, Majority Leader Says
